public enum SvgTransformCmd
extends java.lang.Enum<SvgTransformCmd>
Command that describes how to transform a shape in the attribute of a node in scalable vector graphics (SVG).

  • Enum Constant Details

    • MATRIX

      public static final SvgTransformCmd MATRIX
      Uses a 2x3 affine transform matrix. The data are ordered as (0.) right x, (1.) right y, (2.) up x, (3.) up y, (4.) translation x, (5.) translation y.

    • ROTATE

      public static final SvgTransformCmd ROTATE
      A rotate command takes 1-3 data points. If the pivot x and y are not defined, they are assumed to be (0, 0).

    • SCALE

      public static final SvgTransformCmd SCALE
      A scale command takes 1-2 data points. If height is not defined, it is assumed to be equal to width.

    • SKEW_X

      public static final SvgTransformCmd SKEW_X
      A skew x command takes 1 data point.

    • SKEW_Y

      public static final SvgTransformCmd SKEW_Y
      A skew y command takes 1 data point.

    • TRANSLATE

      public static final SvgTransformCmd TRANSLATE
      A translate command takes 1-2 data points. If y is not defined, it is assumed to be zero.
